Agreed. For context the example always giving is no betting on Jr hockey - because you know... Canada.
Side note: I’m so happy it wasn’t 8 seconds longer. Then we’d have to say “6 min” and who would watch that??

Overwatch League is 18+. Counter-Strike is 18+. League of Legends is 16+. And in Korea, kids get really serious about gaming at 12 - it’s not comparable to here. So it’s not all under 18 - you choose where to hedge bets.
I wholly agree the growth in this segment is explosive. Love it.
In Canada it’s considered under novelty betting (like a trial) and not subject to parlay betting. This will not last (meaning it’s better now, than it will be).

With sport betting being a core aspect of the long term growth, the real hard truth that betting on Athletes under 18 is a major stumbling block in regulation that is being ignored now - but absolutely will come to the fore.
